job_summary:
Bulletproof, an innovative and expanding Cyber Security specialist, is looking to recruit a SOC Analyst, based in our Stevenage office, to support our continued growth. Ideally stemming from an IT Helpdesk or related background, our SOC Analyst position provides an exciting opportunity to ensure our clients receive the best possible service whilst protecting their business assets and security. You will help maintain and protect our client’s key business assets from threats and risks by monitoring, detecting, analysing, and responding to security incidents.With the role working alongside our experienced SOC team, this will be an ideal opportunity for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to step into a specialised SOC position. With a key focus on attention to detail and client/stakeholder management, we are looking for someone who is comfortable in a client facing role with the technical skills (training is provided) to triage, respond and resolve to a variety of threats. Please note, this role will be a full-time position on a rotating shift pattern, including weekends, to support our 24/7 operation. Shift times are 7am-3pm, 3pm-11pm, and 11pm-7am. An overview of the main duties has been provided below:

Monitor both customer and internal infrastructure to detect security events and vulnerabilities by using various security tools, SIEM technologies and other security resources;
Analyse and investigate various security events to validate security incidents;
Perform proactive and reactive security incident handling and escalation where appropriate;
Perform vulnerability assessments and provide findings with remediation actions;
Manage, tune and optimise security tools following best practice and other performance metrics;
Respond to customers’ tickets and emails, providing assistance with security related issues efficiently and effectively;
Support a 24/7 shift pattern.

Skillset, Experience and Qualifications;

Previous experience in an IT Helpdesk, IT Support, SOC or related role is essential with the ability to handle and prioritise tickets and issues;
Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Computer Networks, Information Security or other related technical discipline would be highly desirable;
Good knowledge and understanding of networking principles and a variety of operating systems;
Good understanding of virtualisation;
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills;
Experience using SIEM technologies (such as Elastic, Splunk and Logrhythm), firewalls and IDS/IPS technologies would be desirable;
Ability to remain calm under pressure and meet deadlines;
Strong organisational skills with a high attention to detail;
Ability to prioritise and handle multiple tasks at any given time;
Pro-active and enthusiastic with a can do attitude;
Excellent verbal and written English communication skills, with the ability to influence and negotiate;
Passionate about security and networks;
Ability to work on own initiative as well as being a team player.

Location: Bulletproof,SG1 2FP,Stevenage, Stevenage SG1
Job Type: Full-time

Like any other regulated bank, we need to make sure we are managing our risks and controls, and are fully compliant with our regulation. At Monzo we want to do so while continuing with our agile "test and learn" approach to launching products. You'll have a supporting role to help our Risk and Control Discipline make sure we successfully roll out and embed our risk management framework across the 1st line.
 You will be supporting all things Technology Risk & Controls within the 1st line at Monzo, with the focus on Payments and Finance technology risk.
 We are looking for someone who has the desire & passion to work on risk & control within our Platform Collective, which supports Monzo's technology infrastructure, cyber security, data platform, payments technology and finance infrastructure. In particular, experience in Technology or Payments Risk & Control Assessments (including control testing), Audit Management, Regulatory Compliance and Issue & Action management is preferred.
 Teams across the first line in Monzo will turn to you for guidance on how to ensure we are not only compliant with regulations, but also fostering a culture of rigorous thinking and careful controls that distinguish us in both banking and technology. You will be leading the way ensuring key risk indicators are well-defined and understood in a timely manner, incidents are managed, MI and reporting packs are created, and risk & control assessments are completed.
 Monzo is an exciting combination of a bank and tech start-up, started from scratch in February 2015 with the aim of making money work for everyone. We're focused on solving our customers' problems, making their financial lives simpler, and giving them complete control from their smartphones.
 As a Technology Risk & Control Manager for the Platform Collective, you will use your passion for risk and control to support an environment where teams are able to build at pace yet in control.
 You'll spend your time:

Using your technology risk management knowledge to support teams in developing new processes, controls and features by embedding good regulatory and risk practices;
Ensuring awareness of all of the governance related initiatives (issues, incidents & actions) and regulatory or audit deadlines to make sure we don't miss anything;
Leading risk assessments (RCSA) in the 1st line and driving actions to address the root causes that persistently lead to operational risk losses by challenging both historical and proposed practices;
Leading and performing technology controls testing, remediation and implementation;
Escalating, managing and reporting control issues with transparency;
Ensuring we comply with our policies and help define them where necessary;
Acting as a key stakeholder managing & fostering positive relationships across the three lines of defence on any deficiencies or control gaps across Monzo as needed;
Innovating and finding new ways to build effective governance and risk management processes;

You should apply if:

You have worked in UK banking or fintech, with experience in technology/payments technology risk from 1LOD or Audit.
You are familiar with Payments regulations and requirements
You are a team player and collaborate well with other people.
You are a master communicator, able to facilitate discussions, influence to get buy or push back when needed
You have a good understanding of industry risk standards and practices;
You have experience in technology and/or payments risk management;
You have experience managing multiple deadlines through to completion and have excellent attention to detail;
Are excited about helping Monzo scale in a compliant, thoughtful and controlled way;
You're resilient and comfortable working in a fast paced and ambiguous environment where the day to day job is constantly evolving and changing;
You are hands-on and great at execution;
You are able to meet people where they are at and become a bridge between internal teams and represent Monzo before auditors, regulators and our board;
You are a self-starter and autonomous, able to make prioritisation decisions

Above all, we are looking for people that are excited by what we are doing at Monzo.
 Logistics

This role can be based in our London office (hybrid for now) or remote within the UK as long as you're comfortable travelling to London when required
We offer flexible working hours and trust you to work enough hours to do your job well, at times that suit you and your team.

Diversity and inclusion is a priority for us – if we want to solve problems for people around the world, our team has to represent our customers. So we need to attract the best talent and create an environment that supports and includes them. You can read more about diversity and inclusion on our blog.
 The application process consists of a 30 mins phone call with a recruiter, an initial call with someone from the team, followed by 2 x 45 minute interviews via hangouts. We promise not to ask you any brain teasers or trick questions.
 Equal Opportunity Statement

At Monzo, embracing diversity in all of its forms and fostering an inclusive environment for all people to do the best work of their lives with us. This is integral to our mission of making money work for everyone.
 We're an equal opportunity employer. All applicants will be considered for employment without attention to ethnicity, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, family or parental status, national origin, veteran, neurodiversity status or disability status.

